<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=758&amp;p=7105#p7105"><![CDATA[
Not to mention this would require building a VM into every emulator... seriously restricting how the emulator operates and limiting the kinds of optimizations emu authors can make... on top of slowing down emulation by bringing it a layer of abstraction higher than it needs to be.<br /><br />Hardware emulation should definatly be left to the emulator.  And yes... emulating mappers is part of emulating.  "simulating non-CPU hardware", as you put it, is part of emulation (PPU, APU, controllers, mappers, etc -- everything except for software must be done by the emulator).  In fact... "simulating hardware" is pretty much the <em>definition</em> of emulation.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=33">Disch</a> — Wed Nov 30, 2005 2:02 pm</p><hr />
